13 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 85.59a of Title 74, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. Except as provided under subsection D of this section, the
17 following companies shall be ineligible to bid on or submit a
18 proposal for a contract with a state agency or political subdivision
19 of this state for goods or services:
20 1. A state-owned enterprise of a foreign adversary;
21 2. A foreign adversary company; or
22 3. A federally banned corporation.
23 B. A state agency or any political subdivision of this state
24 shall require a company that submits a bid or proposal with respect
SB997 HFLR Page 5
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 to a contract for goods or services to certify that the company is
2 not a company listed under subsection A of this section.
3 C. If the Director of Office of Management and Enterprise
4 Services or political subdivision determines that a company has
5 submitted a false certification under subsection B of this section:
6 1. The company shall be liable for a civil penalty in an amount
7 that is equal to Two Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars ($250,000.00) or
8 twice the amount of the contract for which a bid or proposal was
9 submitted, whichever is greater;
10 2. The state agency or the Office of Management and Enterprise
11 Services shall terminate the contract with the company; and
12 3. The company shall be ineligible to, and shall not, bid on a
13 state contract for sixty (60) months.
14 D. Notwithstanding the provisions of subsection B of this
15 section, a state agency may enter into a contract for goods
16 manufactured by a company listed under subsection A of this section
17 if:
18 1. There is no other reasonable option for procuring the good;
19 2. The contract is pre-approved by the Director of the Office
